  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Chakra Control (Body)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 5 (Spell Level 3)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 1</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 17 | <b>Successes:</b> 1</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 5 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 16</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, E</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You create a current of spinning Chakra in your hand which knocks a touched creature or unattended object back 5 ft. If a creature encounters a solid surface while being pushed back, it suffers 1d3 nonlethal damage for every 5 ft. of knockback remaining. The surface suffers the same damage. If the target was a held object, its holder can make a Strength check (DC 16) to keep hold of it. If it fails, the object lands in a square of your choice, within 5 ft. Equipment that aids against being disarmed may grant the target bonuses or make it impossible for it to lose its grip on the object (GMs discretion).</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Empower:</b> Spend 1 Chakra to increase the knockback distance by 5 ft. (maximum 50 ft., or 25 ft. for a held object) and increase the Strength check DC to keep hold of an object by 1. Every 3 Chakra spent on this technique (total) increases its Perform Requirements by 1.</p>\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
